Below is an instruction that describes a task. Write a response that appropriately completes the request.

### Instruction:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone.  After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while, and he could only type 6 words per minute. What is the difference between the number of words he could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm

### Response:

Before Cam broke his right arm, he was able to type 9 words per minute on his phone using both hands (right hand for typing). After he broke his arm, he had to use his left hand for a while. He could only type 6 words per minute with the help of his left hand. The difference between the number of words he typed in 5 minutes before and after breaking his arm is 12 words - 9 = 3 words/minute (before) vs. 18 words - 6 = 12 words/minute (after).
